This paper addresses the problem of semantic labeling of RGB-D scenes using deep convolutional neural networks and contextual information. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CV and cs.AI sub-categories. The use of LSTM-CF model for context modeling and fusion is a novel approach, which may also fall under the cs.LG sub-category. The application of this technique to perceptual robotics suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.RO sub-category. Finally, the use of end-to-end training and deep learning techniques may also suggest the cs.NE sub-category.
